==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Reticule
<hw>Ret"i*cule</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n..</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>r⟦eacute⟧ticule</ets>, L. <ets>reticulum</ets>, dim. of
<ets>rete</ets> a net. Cf.<er>Retina</er>, <er>Reticle</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A little bag, originally of network; a woman's workbag,
or a little bag to be carried in the hand.</def> <rj><au>De
Quincey.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A system of wires or lines in the focus of a
telescope or other instrument; a reticle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reticulosa</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
